<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>The end of The Bachelor is fast approaching.</p>

<p>And now Locky Gilbert is set to face his toughest challenge yet as he meets the families of his final four contenders during next week's hometown visits.</p>

<p>If the show's new teaser trailer is anything to go by, the 31-year-old hunk is about to be grilled by each of the girls' protective parents.</p>

<p>'Is this really love?' In a new teaser trailer for The Bachelor, Locky Gilbert gets grilled by protective family members about his reality television past during next week's home visits </p>

<p>At one point, Locky's reality television past appears to have caught up with him.</p>

<p>'Okay, so this is your third reality TV show, is this really love?' one family member is heard asking in the preview. </p>

<p>Another questions his views on feminism, to which Locky explains: 'I'm on The Bachelor, some people might think I'm not the best guy to talk about feminism.'</p>

<p>The Australian Survivor star also visited Bella Varelis' family, where her father issues a stern warning.</p>

<p>Tough questions: 'Okay, so this is your third reality TV show, is this really love?' one family member is heard asking in the preview </p>

<p>'There's gonna be some hearts broken and the only heart that I care about is hers...' he warns.</p>

<p>To which, Locky replies: 'I totally understand that.' </p>

<p>On Thursday night, Kaitlyn Hoppe was left heartbroken after she failed to get a rose from the handsome hunk. </p>

<p>Careful now! The Australian Survivor star also visited Bella Varelis' family, where her father issued a stern warning</p>

<p>The remaining women competing for Locky's affections are Irena Srbinovska, Bella Varelis, Bec Cvilikas and Izzy Sharman-Firth.</p>

<p>Bella and Irena are currently tipped to be the final two ladies vying for Locky's heart. </p>

<p>The Bachelor continues Wednesday at 7:30pm on Channel 10   </p>

<p>Will she win? The remaining women competing for Locky's affections are Irena Srbinovska, Bella Varelis (pictured), Bec Cvilikas and Izzy Sharman-Firth</p>
